&gt; &gt; find a way to do it...
&gt; 
&gt; This is the Parametrised Test pattern thingy, isn&#39;t it?
&gt; 
&gt; * suppose your test class is TestSpoo.
&gt; 
&gt; * give the TestSpoo constructor an [extra] argument:
&gt; 
&gt;     public TestSpoo( [String nameIfLegacy,] String primKey ) ...
&gt; 
&gt; * remember the primKey in a field of TestSpoo
&gt; 
&gt;     protected String primKey;
&gt; 
&gt; * use the field in your test case:
&gt; 
&gt;     public void testAdd() { testAdd( primKey ); /* or inline */ }
&gt; 
&gt; * when you construct the test suite, add specific TestSpoo 
instances to
&gt;   it:
&gt; 
&gt;      TestSuite answer = ...
&gt;      answer.addTest( new TestSpoo( [legacy,] &quot;somePrimKey&quot; );
&gt;      answer.addTest( new TestSpoo( [legacy,] &quot;someOtherPrimKey&quot; );
&gt; 
